Package org.training.foodorderapplication.dto

package org.training.foodorderapplication.dto
This package contains Data Transfer Object (DTO) classes for the Food Order Application. The DTOs are used to transfer data between the application and clients via the RESTful API.

The package contains the following classes:

ApiResponse - represents the response of an API request, containing a status message and a response body.

AuthenticationRequest - represents an authentication request from a client, containing the user's login credentials.

AuthenticationResponse - represents the response to an authentication request, containing a JWT token to authenticate future requests.

Constant - provides constants used throughout the application, such as error messages and response status codes.

FoodItemDto - represents a food item in the application, containing details such as name, description, price, etc.

FoodQuantityDto - represents a quantity of a food item in an order, containing the item ID and quantity.

RegistrationRequest - represents a registration request from a client, containing the user's registration details.

Response - represents a response from the server, containing a status code and message.

VendorDto - represents a vendor in the application, containing details such as name, address, phone number, etc.

By using these DTO classes, the application is able to transfer data between clients and the system via the RESTful API.
